# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Vaulte Digital Banking — Environment Variables
#  Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
#  NEVER commit .env.local to version control.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── App URL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used for generating password reset links in emails.
# In development, use http://localhost:3001
# In production, use your deployed URL.
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://vaulteapp.com

# ─── Resend (System Email — no-reply@vaulteapp.com) ──────────
# Used for: verification codes, login OTPs, password resets,
# new-login alerts, and the welcome email.
#
# Sign up at https://resend.com (free tier: 3,000 emails/month)
# 1. Create an account at resend.com
# 2. Go to API Keys → Create API Key
# 3. Paste it here
# 4. Verify your sending domain (vaulteapp.com) in Resend
#    so the no-reply@vaulteapp.com address is authorized.
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─── Zoho Mail SMTP (Support Email — support@vaulteapp.com) ──
# Used for: customer support tickets, acknowledgements, and
# branded admin replies.  These send from / land in your real
# Zoho mailbox, so threads work normally and you can hit Reply
# in Zoho to respond directly to the customer.
#
# Setup steps in Zoho:
#   1. Subscribe to Zoho Mail (Lite is enough — gives you 1 user / 5 GB).
#   2. Verify the domain vaulteapp.com (Domains → Add Domain).
#   3. Create the mailbox support@vaulteapp.com.
#   4. Add SPF, DKIM, and DMARC DNS records exactly as Zoho instructs.
#   5. Generate an APP-SPECIFIC password:
#        Zoho Mail → Settings → Security → App Passwords →
#        Generate New Password → name it "Vaulte SMTP".
#      Copy the 16-character password (NOT your Zoho login password).
#
# Pick the host for your region:
#   smtp.zoho.com   — global / US (default)
#   smtp.zoho.eu    — EU
#   smtp.zoho.in    — India
ZOHO_SMTP_HOST=smtp.zoho.com
ZOHO_SMTP_PORT=465
ZOHO_SMTP_USER=support@vaulteapp.com
ZOHO_SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-zoho-app-password

# ─── Upstash Redis (OTP & Token Storage) ─────────────────────
# Sign up at https://upstash.com (free tier: 10,000 req/day)
# 1. Create a Redis database at upstash.com
# 2. Choose "Global" for lowest latency
# 3. Copy the REST URL and REST Token from the dashboard
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://xxxxxxx-xxxxx-xxxxx.upstash.io
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=AXxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─── Email Sender Identities ─────────────────────────────────
# Defined in lib/emailService.ts:
#   NOREPLY = "Vaulte <no-reply@vaulteapp.com>"     ← Resend
#   SUPPORT = "Vaulte Support <support@vaulteapp.com>" ← Zoho SMTP
#
# Both addresses must exist on the matching service:
#   no-reply@vaulteapp.com  → authorized in Resend
#   support@vaulteapp.com   → real Zoho mailbox

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  SETUP GUIDE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  QUICK START (Development):
#  1. Copy: cp .env.example .env.local
#  2. Get Resend API key from resend.com (free)
#  3. Get Upstash Redis credentials from upstash.com (free)
#  4. Set up Zoho Mail Lite for support@vaulteapp.com
#  5. Update env vars above
#  6. Run: npm run dev
#
#  VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
#  Go to Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#  and add EVERY variable from this file (including the four ZOHO_* ones).
#  Or run from CLI:
#    vercel env add RESEND_API_KEY
#    vercel env add ZOHO_SMTP_HOST
#    vercel env add ZOHO_SMTP_PORT
#    vercel env add ZOHO_SMTP_USER
#    vercel env add ZOHO_SMTP_PASS
#    vercel env add UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL
#    vercel env add UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN
#    vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL
#
#  RESEND DOMAIN SETUP (no-reply@):
#  1. Log into resend.com → Domains → Add Domain → vaulteapp.com
#  2. Add the DNS records Resend provides to your DNS host
#  3. Wait for verification (15 min – 48 hrs)
#
#  ZOHO MAIL SETUP (support@):
#  1. Log into mail.zoho.com → Subscribe to Mail Lite
#  2. Add domain vaulteapp.com (verify with TXT record)
#  3. Create user support@vaulteapp.com
#  4. Add the SPF, DKIM, and DMARC records Zoho gives you
#     ⚠ Without these, Gmail/Outlook will junk every reply.
#  5. Settings → Security → App Passwords → "Vaulte SMTP" → copy password
#  6. Paste password into ZOHO_SMTP_PASS
#
#  LOGO IN EMAILS:
#  The email templates use:
#  https://vaulteapp.com/assets/logo-vaulte.png
#  This is the publicly hosted logo on your custom domain.
#  If domain changes, update LOGO_URL in lib/emailTemplates.ts
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
